our takeover of Eastern Europe,

692
00:42:18,336 --> 00:42:20,538
以及柏林墙的修建
and the construction of the Berlin Wall.

693
00:42:24,275 --> 00:42:26,812
你知道我们的床要舒服得多
You know our bed's a lot more comfortable.

694
00:42:26,945 --> 00:42:30,348
除非你更喜欢
惠特克·钱伯斯而不是我？
Well, unless you prefer, uh, Whittaker Chambers to me?

695
00:42:30,481 --> 00:42:32,684
哦，你知道那不是真的
Oh, you know that's not true.

696
00:42:32,818 --> 00:42:34,920
来床上吧，亲爱的时间不早了
Come to bed, honey. It's late.

697
00:42:39,357 --> 00:42:43,762
你知道，他们只有导弹和石油
You know, all they have are missiles and oil.

698
00:42:44,863 --> 00:42:47,232
如果我们让他们花掉他们没有的钱，
If we get them to spend money they don't have,

699
00:42:47,365 --> 00:42:48,734
他们就无法维持自己
they can't support themselves.

700
00:42:48,867 --> 00:42:50,769
- 苏联人 - 苏联人
- The Soviets. - The Soviets.

701
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:52,738
我们一直在用错误的方式
处理这个问题
We've been going about this all wrong.

702
00:42:52,871 --> 00:42:55,440
我们不需要在导弹上与他们一一对应
We don't have to match them missile for missile.

703
00:42:56,307 --> 00:42:58,176
我们所要做的
All we have to do

704
00:42:58,309 --> 00:43:00,411
只是保持压力
is just keep up the pressure.

705
00:43:00,545 --> 00:43:02,881
我们的口袋比他们深
We have deeper pockets than they do.

706
00:43:03,014 --> 00:43:05,884
我还以为我嫁给了一个演员呢
And here I thought,I married an actor.

707
00:43:07,152 --> 00:43:09,855
嗯，你可以随时和迪克·尼克松谈谈，
Well, you could always talk to Dick Nixon,

708
00:43:09,988 --> 00:43:13,625
或者肯尼迪总统
或者你的任何政治朋友
President Kennedy, or any of your political friends.

709
00:43:15,393 --> 00:43:18,196
但为什么我的丈夫似乎总能
But why is it that my husband seems to know

710
00:43:18,329 --> 00:43:21,099
比他们更早知道将要发生什么呢，嗯？
what's gonna happen before they do, hmm?

711
00:43:23,001 --> 00:43:25,203
- 嗯... - 是啊
- Well... - Yeah.

712
00:43:25,336 --> 00:43:28,907
我曾是河边公共游泳池的救生员
I was a lifeguard at a public swimming hole on a river.

713
00:43:29,908 --> 00:43:31,743
我研究那条河
And I studied that river.

714
00:43:32,577 --> 00:43:35,747
我学会了如何解读水流
And I learned how to read the currents.

715
00:43:37,415 --> 00:43:40,585
不仅是表面的水流
Not just the ones on the surface.

716
00:43:40,585 --> 00:43:43,655
还有深藏在水下的暗流，
But also the ones that were deep underneath the water,

717
00:43:44,589 --> 00:43:46,557
在水底深处流动
flowing way under.

718
00:43:49,227 --> 00:43:50,662
我在这方面变得很擅长
And I got good at it.

719
00:44:01,539 --> 00:44:03,809
我能在人们意识到之前
察觉到他们有麻烦了
I knew people were in trouble before they did.

720
00:44:14,953 --> 00:44:18,156
穆恩，谢谢你这么快
就把你弟弟带到这里来
Moon, thank you for bringing your brother up here on such short notice.

721
00:44:18,289 --> 00:44:20,358
这不容易，他不喜欢飞行
It wasn't easy, he's not a fan of flying.

722
00:44:20,491 --> 00:44:23,128
好吧，我们会改善这一点的谢谢你来，里根先生
Well, we'll remedy that. Thank you for coming, Mr. Reagan.

723
00:44:23,261 --> 00:44:24,963
谢谢你邀请我，塔特尔先生
Thanks for having me, Mr. Tuttle.

724
00:44:25,096 --> 00:44:27,265
现在，我们听说你跨越了政治鸿沟
Now, we understand that you jumped the aisle

725
00:44:27,398 --> 00:44:29,134
- 换了政党 - 嗯，
- and switched parties. - Well,

726
00:44:29,267 --> 00:44:32,537
我和我哥哥都是在罗斯福时代成长的
my brother and I both, we came of age under FDR.

727
00:44:32,670 --> 00:44:34,639
我们的父亲杰克是他的狂热粉丝，
Our dad, Jack, he was a huge fan,

728
00:44:34,773 --> 00:44:38,276
我们也以新政民主党人的身份为荣
and we were proud to be New Deal Democrats.

729
00:44:38,409 --> 00:44:39,945
那你为什么离开他们？
So why did you leave 'em?

730
00:44:40,078 --> 00:44:41,312
我没有离开
I didn't.

731
00:44:41,446 --> 00:44:43,381
是他们离开了我
They left me.

732
00:44:43,514 --> 00:44:45,550
那么,你对为戈德华特竞选
有什么看法?
Well, how do you feel about campaigning for Goldwater?

733
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:47,052
他11月肯定会惨败
He's gonna get shellacked in November.

734
00:44:47,185 --> 00:44:49,187
他不可能入主白宫
No way he takes the White House.

735
00:44:49,320 --> 00:44:52,623
塔特尔先生说得对
他无法击败林登·约翰逊
Mr. Tuttle's right, he can't beat LBJ.

736
00:44:52,758 --> 00:44:54,525
我很好奇,罗恩
I'm curious, Ron.

737
00:44:54,659 --> 00:44:56,862
你认为我们这个时代的
主要问题是什么?
What would you say is the issue of our time?

738
00:44:58,296 --> 00:45:00,198
毫无疑问
No question about it.

739
00:45:00,331 --> 00:45:02,367
共产主义和苏联
Communism and the Soviet Union.

740
00:45:02,500 --> 00:45:05,636
我更好奇国内问题
Domestic issues is what I'm more curious about.

741
00:45:07,806 --> 00:45:11,709
还有什么比生存更关乎
国内的问题吗,塔特尔先生?
What's more domestic than survival, Mr. Tuttle?

742
00:45:11,843 --> 00:45:14,746
共产主义是自由的天敌
Communism is the natural enemy of freedom.

743
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:18,483
它不会停止从外部或内部攻击我们
It won't stop attacking us from the outside or the inside.

744
00:45:18,616 --> 00:45:21,219
它正在世界各地蔓延,而我们却在
And it's spreading around the world while we wring our hands

745
00:45:21,352 --> 00:45:22,888
试图谈判时束手无策
trying to negotiate.

746
00:45:26,958 --> 00:45:29,895
我跟你们说什么来着,伙计们?
他不只是个花瓶
What did I tell you, guys? He's not just a pretty face.

747
00:45:30,028 --> 00:45:32,263
罗恩,你为什么不用行动
来证明你的观点呢?
Why don't you put your money where your mouth is, Ron?

748
00:45:32,397 --> 00:45:36,067
参与进来支持戈德华特,然后参选
Get in the game. Support Goldwater and then run for office.

749
00:45:36,201 --> 00:45:37,869
嗯,他肯定能以压倒性优势
当选州参议员
Well, he'd win State Senator in a landslide.

750
00:45:38,003 --> 00:45:39,905
州参议员听起来怎么样?
State Senator. How does that sound?

751
00:45:42,974 --> 00:45:43,875
嗯,
Well,

752
00:45:44,910 --> 00:45:46,377
我曾经扮演过参议员
I played a senator once.

753
00:45:48,579 --> 00:45:50,248
但我从未扮演过州长
But I've never played a governor.

754
00:45:56,988 --> 00:46:01,059
在我开始关注他十七年后,
Seventeen years after,I had begun following him,

755
00:46:01,226 --> 00:46:05,030
他在美国政治舞台上首次亮相
he made his debut on American political stage.

756
00:46:05,196 --> 00:46:08,433
我想告诉你们
其实并不存在左派或右派
Well, I'd like to suggest to you, there is no such thing as left or right.

757
00:46:08,566 --> 00:46:10,635
只有向上或向下
There's only up or down.

758
00:46:10,802 --> 00:46:12,370
- 看,那是爸爸
- 我认为我们面临的问题
- Look, there's daddy. -  I believe that the issues

759
00:46:12,537 --> 00:46:14,405
跨越了党派界限
confronting us cross party lines.

760
00:46:14,572 --> 00:46:16,474
现在,这场竞选的一方
Now, one side of this campaign

761
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:19,077
一直在告诉我们,这次选举的问题
has been telling us that the issues of this election

762
00:46:19,210 --> 00:46:21,646
是维持和平与繁荣
are the maintenance of peace and prosperity.

763
00:46:22,680 --> 00:46:24,649
他们用的说辞是:
The line has been used.

764
00:46:24,782 --> 00:46:26,717
"我们从未如此富足"
"We've never had it so good."

765
00:46:26,852 --> 00:46:30,321
某种程度上,这是一种扭曲
Somewhere, a perversion has taken place.

766
00:46:30,455 --> 00:46:33,391
难道摩西应该告诉以色列的子民
Should Moses have told the children of Israel to live

767
00:46:33,524 --> 00:46:35,093
继续在法老统治下做奴隶吗?
in slavery under the pharaohs?

768
00:46:35,226 --> 00:46:37,228
难道基督应该拒绝十字架吗?
Should Christ have refused the cross?

769
00:46:37,362 --> 00:46:39,230
难道爱国者们应该放下枪支,
Should the patriots have thrown down their guns

770
00:46:39,364 --> 00:46:42,067
拒绝发出那响彻世界的一枪吗?
and refused to fire the shot heard around the world?

771
00:46:43,301 --> 00:46:45,470
你我都有勇气
You and I have the courage

772
00:46:45,603 --> 00:46:47,805
对我们的敌人说...
to say to our enemies...

773
00:46:47,973 --> 00:46:50,308
我们不会付出某些代价
there is a price we will not pay.

774
00:46:50,475 --> 00:46:56,214
有一个界限他们不能跨越
A point beyond which they must not advance.

775
00:46:56,381 --> 00:46:58,917
我们会为我们的孩子保存这个，
We'll preserve for our children this,

776
00:46:59,084 --> 00:47:01,619
人类在地球上最后最好的希望，
the last best hope of man on Earth,

777
00:47:01,786 --> 00:47:04,990
否则我们将判处他们迈出最后一步
or we'll sentence them to take the last step

778
00:47:05,156 --> 00:47:07,692
进入千年的黑暗
into a thousand years of darkness.

779
00:47:08,326 --> 00:47:11,196
当世界上伟大的力量在移动时，
When great forces are on the move in the world,

780
00:47:11,329 --> 00:47:16,534
我们意识到我们是精神，而不是动物
we learn that we are spirits, not animals.

781
00:47:16,667 --> 00:47:19,537
在时间和空间中，
There's something going on in time and space,

782
00:47:19,670 --> 00:47:21,506
超越时间和空间，
beyond time and space,

783
00:47:21,639 --> 00:47:23,474
无论我们喜欢与否，
which, whether we like it or not,

784
00:47:23,608 --> 00:47:25,276
都意味着责任
spells duty.

785
00:47:26,111 --> 00:47:27,045
你和我...
You and I...

786
00:47:28,413 --> 00:47:30,615
与命运有一场约会
have a rendezvous with destiny.

787
00:47:35,186 --> 00:47:38,056
戈德华特先生败得很惨
Mr. Goldwater lost decisively.

788
00:47:38,856 --> 00:47:41,859
但十字军战士已经到来
But The Crusader had arrived.

789
00:47:42,027 --> 00:47:46,898
他正在警告我们
他不怕与我们对抗
And he was putting us on notice that he was not afraid to take us on.

790
00:47:56,841 --> 00:47:57,808
- 你好 - 你好
- Hello. - Hello.

791
00:47:57,943 --> 00:47:59,877
哦，嗨！是你啊！
Oh, hi! It's you!

792
00:48:00,011 --> 00:48:02,680
- 嗯，是的
- 你在这里做什么？
-  Well, yes. - What are doing you here?

793
00:48:02,813 --> 00:48:04,349
我...我赢得了什么吗？
I-- Did I win something?

794
00:48:04,482 --> 00:48:06,751
不是我们正在走访这个社区，
No. We're canvasing the neighborhood,

795
00:48:06,884 --> 00:48:09,754
我正在竞选州长
我想请你投我一票
and I'm running for governor and I would like your vote.

796
00:48:09,887 --> 00:48:12,757
哦，当然！当然！我...
Well, of course! Of course! I...

797
00:48:13,458 --> 00:48:15,860
现在我觉得很尴尬
我忘了你的名字
Now I'm embarrassed. I forgot your name.

798
00:48:15,994 --> 00:48:18,863
他的首字母能帮上忙吗？RR？
Do his initials help? RR?

799
00:48:20,966 --> 00:48:24,535
亲爱的！罗伊·罗杰斯来了！
Honey! Roy Rogers is here!

800
00:48:26,537 --> 00:48:28,839
而且他在竞选州长！
And he's running for governor!

801
00:48:44,455 --> 00:48:46,891
他现在已经站在美国的舞台上了
He was on the US stage now.

802
00:48:48,193 --> 00:48:51,529
但我的同事们仍然拒绝
认真对待他
But my colleagues still refused to take him seriously.

803
00:48:52,397 --> 00:48:53,698
毕竟，他们说，
After all, they said,

804
00:48:54,765 --> 00:48:56,968
"一个州长能对我们做什么呢？"
"What could state governor do to us?"

805
00:48:57,102 --> 00:48:59,971
里根！里根！
Reagan! Reagan!

806
00:49:02,707 --> 00:49:05,310
警察负担过重他们太多了
The police are overburdened. There's just too many of them.

807
00:49:05,443 --> 00:49:07,112
这些孩子的父母在哪里？
Where are these kids' parents?

808
00:49:07,245 --> 00:49:09,280
嗯，他们不全是学生
大多是煽动者
Well, they're not all students. Mostly agitators.

809
00:49:09,414 --> 00:49:10,915
他们甚至不知道自己在抗议什么
They don't even know what they're protesting.

810
00:49:11,049 --> 00:49:12,717
他们只是为了抗议而抗议，
They're just doing it to do it,

811
00:49:12,850 --> 00:49:14,219
而且他们得到了外部帮助
and they're getting outside help.

812
00:49:14,352 --> 00:49:15,653
他们提出了一系列新的要求
They've issued a new set of demands.

813
00:49:15,786 --> 00:49:17,288
他们当然会这样做
Of course they have.

814
00:49:17,422 --> 00:49:19,657
他们希望你亲自向他们展示
They want you to present them to them personally.

815
00:49:20,691 --> 00:49:23,428
国民警卫队已经待命
The National Guard... is on standby.

816
00:49:23,561 --> 00:49:25,130
他们可以在一小时内到达现场
They can be on-site within an hour.

817
00:49:25,263 --> 00:49:27,832
那就是联邦介入了会有影响的
That's going federal. Ramifications for that.

818
00:49:27,965 --> 00:49:30,968
社区、学校，尤其是媒体
Communities, schools, especially the press.

819
00:49:32,270 --> 00:49:33,638
如果他们想谈,
If they wanna talk,

820
00:49:35,106 --> 00:49:36,441
那就去谈吧
let's go talk.

821
00:49:48,219 --> 00:49:49,354
爱情万岁！
Love rules!

822
00:49:49,487 --> 00:49:52,657
里根州长！要爱不要战！
Governor Reagan! Make love, not war!

823
00:49:52,790 --> 00:49:55,993
看他现在的样子，两样都做不到
From the looks of him, he can't do either right now.

824
00:49:56,127 --> 00:49:57,962
比尔会在里面跟我们会合
Bill's gonna meet us inside.

825
00:49:59,230 --> 00:50:00,165
带路吧
Lead the way.

826
00:50:01,066 --> 00:50:03,368
现在要和平！现在要和平！
Peace now! Peace now!

827
00:50:03,501 --> 00:50:06,604
我们想听你公开向加州人民讲话！
We want to hear you speak openly about this to the state of California!

828
00:50:06,737 --> 00:50:08,639
你认为我来这里是在干什么？
Well, what do you think,I'm doing here?

829
00:50:08,773 --> 00:50:11,809
如果你能出面反对警察升级行动
他们可能会听
If you would come out against the police escalation, they might listen.

830
00:50:11,942 --> 00:50:15,446
你什么时候在你的学生面前站出来
When did you ever stand up in front of your students

831
00:50:15,580 --> 00:50:17,148
恳求他们不要这样做？
and beg them not to do this?

832
00:50:17,282 --> 00:50:20,851
他们告诉你，如果你继续进行这项建设，
They told you that they were going to destroy the university

833
00:50:20,985 --> 00:50:23,288
他们就会摧毁大学
if you sought to go ahead with this construction.

834
00:50:23,421 --> 00:50:26,391
- 但他们提出要谈判！ - 谈判什么？
- But they offered to negotiate! - Negotiate what?

835
00:50:26,524 --> 00:50:28,626
教授，这一切发生的时候，
All of this happened, professor, the very first time

836
00:50:28,759 --> 00:50:30,628
你们这些年纪大到应该懂事的人
that some of you who are old enough to know better

837
00:50:30,761 --> 00:50:34,165
第一次让学生们认为他们有权选择
let students think that they have the right to choose

838
00:50:34,299 --> 00:50:36,134
遵守哪些法律，
which laws they were gonna obey,

839
00:50:36,267 --> 00:50:39,003
只要是以社会抗议的名义进行的
as long as it was done in the name of social protest.

840
00:50:39,137 --> 00:50:40,705
我受够了
I've had enough.

841
00:50:42,373 --> 00:50:44,909
我要调动国民警卫队
I'm calling in the National Guard.

842
00:51:03,694 --> 00:51:05,062
嘘！
Shh!

843
00:51:12,537 --> 00:51:14,572
抗议者对他施加了很大压力，
The protestors pushed him hard,

844
00:51:14,705 --> 00:51:16,341
但他反击得更猛烈
but he pushed them harder.

845
00:51:17,308 --> 00:51:19,777
他是个有争议的州长，
He was controversial governor,

846
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:21,779
但能做的事情有限
but limited in what he could accomplish.

847
00:51:21,912 --> 00:51:25,883
至少在他最关心的事情上是这样
比如我们
At least, as far as the things he cared most about, like us.

848
00:51:27,652 --> 00:51:30,421
他激怒了许多同情我们事业的人，
He enraged many sympathetic to our cause,

849
00:51:30,555 --> 00:51:33,358
但他也激励了许多狂热分子，
but he also inspired many fanatics

850
00:51:33,491 --> 00:51:34,892
他们会不惜一切代价
who would go to great lengths

851
00:51:35,059 --> 00:51:37,928
去一睹他们英雄的风采
to get a glimpse of their hero.

852
00:51:39,564 --> 00:51:41,799
罗恩，这是谁？
Ron, who's this?

853
00:51:42,733 --> 00:51:44,034
年轻人，呃...
Young man, uh...

854
00:51:44,935 --> 00:51:46,036
你为什么在我的院子里？
why are you in my yard?

855
00:51:47,605 --> 00:51:48,973
嘿，夫人！
Hey, Mrs. Gov!

856
00:51:49,106 --> 00:51:51,209
我，呃，我是达娜
I'm, uh, I'm Dana.

857
00:51:51,342 --> 00:51:53,411
我是青年支持里根组织的主笔
