01:13:33,877 --> 01:13:35,745
特勤局放我进来的
The Secret Service let me in.

1186
01:13:35,879 --> 01:13:37,246
我是说，你是迈克·迪弗对吧？
I mean, you're Mike Deaver, right?

1187
01:13:40,416 --> 01:13:42,385
一个演讲稿写手？为美国总统...
A speech writer? For the President...

1188
01:13:42,519 --> 01:13:44,087
...工作的？
...of the United States?

1189
01:13:44,220 --> 01:13:47,056
- 我想这里有点...
- 达纳，你终于来了
- I think that there's been... - Dana, you're finally here.

1190
01:13:47,190 --> 01:13:50,193
刚刚飞到，先生
我甚至还没找到住的地方
Just flew in, sir. I don't even have a place to stay yet.

1191
01:13:50,326 --> 01:13:52,729
没有在草坪上过夜，总统先生
Did not spend the night on the lawn, Mr. President.

1192
01:13:52,862 --> 01:13:55,231
- 所以你认识这位先生？ - 是的
- So you know this gentleman? - Yes.

1193
01:13:55,364 --> 01:13:56,633
我们认识很久了
We go way back.

1194
01:13:57,501 --> 01:13:59,102
苏联粮食报告
Soviet grain report.

1195
01:13:59,235 --> 01:14:02,205
睡得好吗？我们来交换一下
Nice nap. I'll trade ya.

1196
01:14:03,873 --> 01:14:05,809
好吧，达纳，我希望你尽快安顿下来
Well, Dana, I want you to hurry up and settle in

1197
01:14:05,942 --> 01:14:07,611
因为我们有很多工作要做
'cause we have a lot of work to do.

1198
01:14:16,920 --> 01:14:17,987
我们这里穿西装
We wear suits here.

1199
01:14:19,556 --> 01:14:21,457
好的，迈克是的
Right on, Mike. Yeah.

1200
01:14:24,460 --> 01:14:27,330
你可能有多余的西装
可以借给我在发薪日前穿吗？
Would you maybe have an extra,I could borrow before payday?

1201
01:14:27,463 --> 01:14:28,397
什--
Wh--

1202
01:14:29,232 --> 01:14:30,266
让我知道
Let me know.

1203
01:14:34,203 --> 01:14:37,140
第一季度的数据低于预期
First quarter numbers are below expectations.

1204
01:14:37,273 --> 01:14:38,842
失业率没有变化
Unemployment hasn't budged.

1205
01:14:38,975 --> 01:14:40,644
我认为我们应该重新审视
I think we should reexamine

1206
01:14:40,777 --> 01:14:43,012
一些摆在桌面上的增收措施，先生
some of the revenue enhancers on the table, sir.

1207
01:14:43,146 --> 01:14:44,648
增收措施？
Revenue enhancers?

1208
01:14:45,749 --> 01:14:48,151
增-- 这就是你们现在在华盛顿
Re-- Is that what you're calling

1209
01:14:48,284 --> 01:14:50,687
称呼增税的方式吗？
tax increases these days in Washington?

1210
01:14:50,820 --> 01:14:53,422
我向美国人民承诺
I told the American people

1211
01:14:53,557 --> 01:14:55,424
我会降低税收
that I would lower taxes.

1212
01:14:55,559 --> 01:14:57,293
所以如果这真的是你的想法，
So if that's what you really think,

1213
01:14:57,426 --> 01:15:00,764
那你他妈在我的政府里做什么？
then what the hell are you doing in my administration?

1214
01:15:00,897 --> 01:15:04,300
总统先生，我们必须平衡这个预算
Mr. President, we simply have to balance this budget.

1215
01:15:04,433 --> 01:15:06,970
你知道，我学到了一两件
关于经济学的事
You know, I've learned a thing or two about economics.

1216
01:15:07,103 --> 01:15:09,472
我在尤里卡学院主修经济学
I majored in Economics at Eureka College.

1217
01:15:09,606 --> 01:15:12,809
虽然不是你们的常春藤盟校，
Now, it wasn't your Ivy League college,

1218
01:15:12,942 --> 01:15:15,444
但我在那里学到了
伊本·赫勒敦的理论，
but there I learned about Ibn Khaldun,

1219
01:15:15,579 --> 01:15:17,547
他是埃及的一位统治者
he was a ruler in Egypt.

1220
01:15:17,681 --> 01:15:19,983
他有一个哲学观点让我很有共鸣，
And he had a philosophy that really hit home

1221
01:15:20,116 --> 01:15:23,820
特别是当我在好莱坞
处于94%的税率阶层时
when I was in the 94% tax bracket in Hollywood.

1222
01:15:23,953 --> 01:15:27,991
那就是当税率较低时，人们会有更多的钱
And that is when taxes are low, people have more money.

1223
01:15:28,124 --> 01:15:31,194
当人们有更多钱时，他们会买更多东西
And when people have more money, they buy more things.

1224
01:15:31,327 --> 01:15:34,631
这些东西必须由其他人制造，
Now, these things have to be made by other people

1225
01:15:34,764 --> 01:15:38,868
而他们又必须雇用更多人来帮助他们做这些事
who have to hire more people to help them do that.

1226
01:15:39,002 --> 01:15:41,404
至于税收，
And as for taxes,

1227
01:15:41,537 --> 01:15:43,640
好吧，上帝只要求10%，
well, the good Lord only asks for 10%,

1228
01:15:43,773 --> 01:15:46,710
为什么山姆大叔要求更多呢？
why should Uncle Sam ask for more?

1229
01:15:46,843 --> 01:15:48,511
总统先生，
Mr. President,

1230
01:15:48,645 --> 01:15:51,147
空中交通管制员威胁要罢工
the Air Traffic Controllers are threatening a strike.

1231
01:15:51,280 --> 01:15:53,249
- 他们可以这么做吗？ - 不行，先生
- Well, can they do that? - No, sir.

1232
01:15:53,382 --> 01:15:54,851
- 从法律上讲？ - 这是必要的公共服务，
- Legally? - Essential public service,

1233
01:15:54,984 --> 01:15:57,587
他们都签了不罢工的合同
they have all signed a no-strike contract.

1234
01:15:57,721 --> 01:15:59,589
合同就是合同
A contract is a contract.

1235
01:16:00,690 --> 01:16:02,592
我就是这么学到的
That's the way I learned it.

1236
01:16:02,726 --> 01:16:04,861
他们丧失了工作
They forfeited their jobs.

1237
01:16:06,763 --> 01:16:11,067
如果他愿意冒险
让自己的国家陷入混乱，
If he was willing to risk chaos in his own country,

1238
01:16:11,234 --> 01:16:14,403
我们只能想象他可能对我们做什么
we could only imagine what he might do to us.

1239
01:16:18,041 --> 01:16:22,011
苏联人正在公开进行全面演习
The Soviets are conducting full exercises right out in the open.

1240
01:16:22,145 --> 01:16:24,347
德国边境很平静，但看起来他们正在
German border is quiet but it looks like they're moving

1241
01:16:24,480 --> 01:16:26,549
通过铁路运送一些全新的SS-20导弹
some brand new SS-20s by rail.

1242
01:16:26,683 --> 01:16:29,385
已经确认了它们在柏林以东20英里处
That's confirmed. They're 20 miles east of Berlin.

1243
01:16:30,486 --> 01:16:33,790
每节火车车厢
都装有一枚带核弹头的弹道导弹
Each rail car contains a ballistic missile with a nuclear warhead.

1244
01:16:33,923 --> 01:16:36,459
约翰，他们有多少枚核导弹？
John, how many nuclear missiles do they have?

1245
01:16:36,592 --> 01:16:37,761
三万五千枚
Thirty-five thousand.

1246
01:16:37,894 --> 01:16:39,896
- 官方数字 - 那我们呢？
- Officially. - And us?

1247
01:16:40,029 --> 01:16:41,731
两万五千多一点，先生
Twenty-five and change, sir.

1248
01:16:41,865 --> 01:16:45,234
所以大约有6万枚核弹头
So roughly 60,000 nuclear warheads

1249
01:16:45,368 --> 01:16:48,137
互相对准
每一枚都能摧毁一座城市
pointed at each other, each one can take out a city.

1250
01:16:48,271 --> 01:16:50,106
差不多就是这样，总统先生
That's about the size of it, Mr. President.

1251
01:16:50,239 --> 01:16:52,375
所以在过去十年里，
So while we have been,

1252
01:16:52,508 --> 01:16:55,111
当我们一直在削减军事力量时，
over the past ten years, reducing our military,

1253
01:16:55,244 --> 01:16:57,146
他们一直在增加他们的武器库，
they've been building up their arsenal

1254
01:16:57,280 --> 01:16:59,315
并对我们嗤之以鼻，
and thumbing their noses at us,

1255
01:16:59,448 --> 01:17:02,418
违反我们与他们签订的每一项条约
violating every treaty that we have with them.

1256
01:17:02,551 --> 01:17:04,788
不仅有可能，先生，这正是正在发生的事情
More than possible, sir, that's exactly what's happening.

1257
01:17:04,921 --> 01:17:08,792
除了拍照记录之外，我们对此做了什么？
And what have we done about it except take a picture of it?

1258
01:17:08,925 --> 01:17:11,761
好吧，在你发射完前一千枚左右后，
Well, after you fire off the first thousand or so,

1259
01:17:11,895 --> 01:17:14,097
就没人能继续计分了，不是吗？
there's no one around to keep score, is there?

1260
01:17:14,230 --> 01:17:15,231
这太疯狂了
It's insane.

1261
01:17:16,365 --> 01:17:19,736
一个小失误,有人喝了太多伏特加,
One little mistake, somebody has too much vodka,

1262
01:17:21,104 --> 01:17:22,305
这一切都不重要了
none of this matters.

1263
01:17:28,878 --> 01:17:30,714
今天成千上万的人
聚集在梵蒂冈的圣彼得广场,
Thousands were gathered in St. Peter's Square

1264
01:17:30,880 --> 01:17:34,317
欢呼教皇的到来
at the Vatican today, cheering the arrival of the Pope.

1265
01:17:34,483 --> 01:17:38,121
但很快,枪声将庆祝变成了恐怖,
But soon, gunshots turn the celebration into horror,

1266
01:17:38,287 --> 01:17:41,791
教皇倒在了他的助手怀里
as the Pope collapsed into the arms of his aids.

1267
01:17:41,925 --> 01:17:44,427
他正在接受手术官方说法是
He's in surgery. The official story

1268
01:17:44,560 --> 01:17:46,930
他只是擦伤,但实际情况更糟
is that he was grazed but it's worse than that.

1269
01:17:47,063 --> 01:17:49,265
他们已经为他做了临终祷告
They gave him his last rites.

1270
01:17:50,333 --> 01:17:51,801
我们了解到什么?
What do we know?

1271
01:17:51,935 --> 01:17:53,636
约翰·保罗来自苏联控制下的波兰
John Paul is from Poland under Soviet control.

1272
01:17:53,770 --> 01:17:55,772
波兰人民渴望自治和民主
Polish people want self-rule and democracy.

1273
01:17:55,905 --> 01:17:57,974
团结工会运动正在席卷全国
Solidarity movement is taking over the nation.

1274
01:17:58,107 --> 01:18:00,276
教皇站在他们这边,
The Pope is with them,

1275
01:18:00,409 --> 01:18:03,046
基本上是在向莫斯科竖中指
因为他可以这么做
basically giving Moscow the middle finger because he can.

1276
01:18:03,179 --> 01:18:05,982
他回祖国访问基本上就像第二次降临
Visit to the homeland is basically the second coming.

1277
01:18:06,115 --> 01:18:09,285
事情很明显,这是莫斯科
通过保加利亚做的,总统先生
The writing's on the wall, this comes from Moscow via Bulgaria, Mr. President.

1278
01:18:09,418 --> 01:18:11,320
这绝对是克格勃的手笔
This is KGB all the way.

1279
01:18:11,454 --> 01:18:13,056
嗯,这说不通,比尔
Well, that doesn't make sense, Bill.

1280
01:18:13,189 --> 01:18:14,958
他们要么会创造一个殉道者,
They're either gonna create a martyr

1281
01:18:15,091 --> 01:18:17,861
要么会激起天主教会
or they're gonna unleash the Catholic Church

1282
01:18:17,994 --> 01:18:19,228
对他们的反抗
against themselves.

1283
01:18:22,832 --> 01:18:23,900
他们害怕了
They're scared.

1284
01:18:25,101 --> 01:18:26,369
教皇活下来了
The Pope lived.

1285
01:18:27,703 --> 01:18:29,773
现在,这位十字军战士和教皇
And now, The Crusader and the Pope

1286
01:18:29,939 --> 01:18:33,109
因为都从刺客的子弹下
幸存而建立了联系
shared a bond of having survived an assassin's bullet.

1287
01:18:33,276 --> 01:18:38,214
而他的新盟友恰好有10亿追随者
And his new ally just happened to have a billion followers.

1288
01:19:08,511 --> 01:19:10,046
离开波兰
Get out of Poland.

1289
01:19:10,213 --> 01:19:11,647
离开阿富汗
Get out of Afghanistan.

1290
01:19:11,815 --> 01:19:13,749
放弃十年来的条约
Throw away ten years of treaties

1291
01:19:13,917 --> 01:19:17,386
并消除所有核导弹
and eliminate all nuclear missiles.

1292
01:19:17,553 --> 01:19:21,457
用美国人的话说
勃列日涅夫的脑子都被震惊了
As they say in America, Brezhnev's mind was blown.

1293
01:19:26,595 --> 01:19:27,596
他在黄色纸上
He scribbles

1294
01:19:28,564 --> 01:19:32,435
给我写了一封私人便条?
a personal note to me on yellow paper?

1295
01:19:32,568 --> 01:19:34,871
给美国总统?
The President of the United States?

1296
01:19:37,006 --> 01:19:38,574
现在我们知道是谁射击他的了
Now we know who shot him.

1297
01:19:40,243 --> 01:19:41,878
他自己的国务院
His own State Department.

1298
01:19:42,011 --> 01:19:44,247
嗯?
Eh?

1299
01:19:44,380 --> 01:19:46,215
不,谢谢
No, thank you.

1300
01:19:50,153 --> 01:19:54,023
现在,他的新国务卿登场了,
And now, enter his new Secretary of State,

1301
01:19:54,190 --> 01:19:58,594
- 乔治·舒尔茨,那个老虎人 - 谁?
- George Shultz, the Tiger Man. -  The who?

1302
01:19:58,727 --> 01:20:01,497
他屁股上有一个老虎纹身
He had a tattoo of a tiger on his ass.

1303
01:20:01,630 --> 01:20:02,798
我们怎么知道的？
How do we know that?

1304
01:20:02,932 --> 01:20:05,101
克格勃在这里
KGB. Here.

1305
01:20:10,739 --> 01:20:13,809
我们就把这个小仪式结束吧
We'll just get this little ceremony over with.

1306
01:20:13,943 --> 01:20:16,946
这是我60年代戒烟时用的
This is what I used to quit smoking back in the '60s.

1307
01:20:18,614 --> 01:20:19,682
哦，我就知道
Oh, I knew it.

1308
01:20:20,950 --> 01:20:23,252
- 我就知道 - 什么？
- I knew it. -  What?

1309
01:20:23,386 --> 01:20:25,688
嗯，你可以从一个人选择
Well, you can tell a lot about a man's character

1310
01:20:25,821 --> 01:20:28,091
是只拿一种颜色
by if he chooses just one color

1311
01:20:28,224 --> 01:20:29,592
还是抓一把看出很多东西
or if he grabs a handful.

1312
01:20:29,725 --> 01:20:31,094
我明白了
I see.

1313
01:20:31,227 --> 01:20:33,262
那么，这说明我的性格如何？
And, uh, what does this say about my character?

1314
01:20:33,396 --> 01:20:35,664
这说明你很专注，
It says that you're focused,

1315
01:20:35,798 --> 01:20:37,366
你很坚定，
you're determined,

1316
01:20:37,500 --> 01:20:39,168
而且你不容易分心
and that you're not easily distracted.

1317
01:20:39,302 --> 01:20:40,636
你在这里会做得很好的
You're gonna do great here.

1318
01:20:41,570 --> 01:20:43,606
好吧，那么
Okay, then.

1319
01:20:43,739 --> 01:20:47,043
美国雇用我们做两件事
America has hired us to do two things.

1320
01:20:47,176 --> 01:20:50,113
让他们再次繁荣，
Let them be prosperous again,

1321
01:20:51,180 --> 01:20:52,548
并保证他们的安全
and keep them safe.

1322
01:20:52,681 --> 01:20:54,283
通过实力获得和平
Peace through strength.

1323
01:20:54,417 --> 01:20:55,518
我可以畅所欲言吗？
May I speak freely?

1324
01:20:55,651 --> 01:20:56,953
我期待你这样做
I expect it.

1325
01:20:57,086 --> 01:20:59,488
清晰就是力量
Clarity is power.

1326
01:20:59,622 --> 01:21:02,491
现在，我相信
你对这些目标很清楚
Now, I believe you are clear in these objectives.

1327
01:21:02,625 --> 01:21:04,493
现在，世界其他地方也需要清楚
Now, the rest of the world needs to be.

1328
01:21:04,627 --> 01:21:06,695
只要这些目标是你的目标
As long as those objectives are your objectives.

1329
01:21:06,829 --> 01:21:08,864
是的，克拉克先生这并不是说
They are, Mr. Clark. Which isn't to say

1330
01:21:08,998 --> 01:21:11,667
如果我看到这些目标有冲突，
that I won't push back or voice opinions

1331
01:21:11,800 --> 01:21:14,170
我就不会反驳或发表意见
if I see conflict in those objectives.

1332
01:21:14,303 --> 01:21:16,039
这正是我选择你的原因
That's exactly why I chose you.

1333
01:21:16,172 --> 01:21:17,907
通过实力获得和平，这有点--
Peace through strength is, it's--

1334
01:21:18,041 --> 01:21:19,742
这有点模糊
It's just a-a bit opaque.

1335
01:21:19,875 --> 01:21:23,412
我需要你阐明一个关于苏联的信息
I-I need you to articulate a message about the Soviets

1336
01:21:23,546 --> 01:21:25,248
让我可以传达给全世界
that I can take to the world.

1337
01:21:26,715 --> 01:21:28,017
嗯，那很简单
Well, that's simple.

1338
01:21:28,952 --> 01:21:30,053
我们赢
We win.

1339
01:21:30,186 --> 01:21:31,420
他们输
They lose.

1340
01:21:31,554 --> 01:21:32,855
你可以引用我的话
And you can quote me.

1341
01:21:35,891 --> 01:21:37,326
嗯，这是一个清晰的信息
Well, that's a clear message.

1342
01:22:07,023 --> 01:22:09,358
- 嘿，达奇，你要去哪？ - 来啊，达奇！
- Hey, Dutch, where you going? - Come on, Dutch!

1343
01:22:10,893 --> 01:22:12,795
- 胆小鬼！ - 四眼仔！
- Scaredy-cat! - Four eyes!

1344
01:22:12,928 --> 01:22:14,430
那就是一直威胁你的男孩？
That's the boy that's been threatening you?

1345
01:22:14,563 --> 01:22:16,599
- 每天都是 - 过来！
-  Every day. -  Get over here!

1346
01:22:18,101 --> 01:22:21,137
- 妈宝男
- 他明天也会在那里
- Mama's boy. - He'll be there tomorrow too.

1347
01:22:21,270 --> 01:22:23,572
这就是恶霸的行为
直到你勇于反抗他们
That's what bullies do until you stand up to them.

1348
01:22:24,573 --> 01:22:26,042
是时候解决这个问题了，达奇
It's time for you to settle this, Dutch.

1349
01:22:27,076 --> 01:22:28,044
去吧
Go on.

1350
01:22:33,016 --> 01:22:34,150
来啊，妈宝男
Come on, Mama's boy.

1351
01:22:40,923 --> 01:22:42,558
打他
Get him.

1352
01:23:14,423 --> 01:23:15,924
有点软
It's a little soft.

1353
01:23:16,959 --> 01:23:18,127
