-  Yes! - We love berry picking.

1506
01:34:53,789 --> 01:34:54,923
- 整个下午都在采？ - 嗯哼！
-  All afternoon? - Mm-hmm!

1507
01:34:55,090 --> 01:34:57,125
- 我们采了成千上万个
- 成千上万个？
-  We picked thousands. - Thousands?

1508
01:34:57,292 --> 01:34:59,094
到处都是浆果
They were all over the place.

1509
01:34:59,261 --> 01:35:00,528
什么种类的浆果？
What kind of berries?

1510
01:35:00,695 --> 01:35:02,464
- 蓝莓，先生 - 蓝莓！
-  Blueberries, sir. - Blueberries!

1511
01:35:02,630 --> 01:35:04,166
- 是的！ - 是的！蓝色的！
- Yes! - Yes! Blue!

1512
01:35:05,500 --> 01:35:08,403
现在，呃，还太早，蓝莓还没熟
It's, uh, too early for blueberries.

1513
01:35:09,772 --> 01:35:11,406
那些是草莓
They were strawberries.

1514
01:35:11,573 --> 01:35:14,810
特雷维特先生，请向里根总统提问
Mr. Trewhitt, your question to President Reagan.

1515
01:35:14,977 --> 01:35:17,946
总统先生
我想提出一个已经潜伏了两三周的问题，
Mr. President, I wanna raise an issue that I think has been lurking out there

1516
01:35:18,113 --> 01:35:20,382
并从国家安全的角度来具体讨论
for two or three weeks, and cast it specifically

1517
01:35:20,515 --> 01:35:22,417
从国家安全的角度来看
in national security terms.

1518
01:35:22,550 --> 01:35:24,887
您已经是历史上年纪最大的总统，
You already are the oldest,President in history

1519
01:35:25,020 --> 01:35:26,721
您的一些幕僚说您在最近与
蒙代尔先生的交锋后感到疲惫
and some of your staff say that you were tired

1520
01:35:26,855 --> 01:35:29,724
与蒙代尔先生最近的交锋后感到疲惫
after your most recent encounter with Mr. Mondale.

1521
01:35:29,858 --> 01:35:32,828
我记得肯尼迪总统在古巴导弹危机期间
I recall yet that President Kennedy had to go for days on end

1522
01:35:32,961 --> 01:35:35,363
不得不连续几天几乎没有睡眠
with very little sleep during the Cuban Missile Crisis.

1523
01:35:35,497 --> 01:35:37,900
您是否有任何疑问，在这种情况下
Is there any doubt in your mind that you would be able to function

1524
01:35:38,033 --> 01:35:39,768
您是否能正常工作？
in such circumstances?

1525
01:35:39,902 --> 01:35:41,870
完全没有问题，特雷维特先生
Not at all, Mr. Trewhitt.

1526
01:35:42,004 --> 01:35:43,705
我也想让您知道，
And I want you to know that, also,

1527
01:35:43,839 --> 01:35:47,342
我不会在这次竞选中把年龄作为一个问题
I will not make age an issue in this campaign.

1528
01:35:47,475 --> 01:35:50,712
我不会为了政治目的，
I will not for political purposes,

1529
01:35:50,846 --> 01:35:54,216
利用我对手的年轻和缺乏经验
exploit my opponent's youth and inexperience.

1530
01:35:58,353 --> 01:36:00,856
就凭这一句机智的话...
And with that one thrust of wit...

1531
01:36:06,394 --> 01:36:07,729
他扭转了局势
he turned the tide.

1532
01:36:20,542 --> 01:36:26,381
美国！美国！美国！美国！
USA, USA, USA, USA!

1533
01:36:28,716 --> 01:36:30,785
- 他会到场的 - 您找我，长官？
- He'll be there. - You wanted to see me, sir?

1534
01:36:31,719 --> 01:36:33,588
不，我们会想办法的
No, we'll figure it out.

1535
01:36:33,721 --> 01:36:35,991
是的，约翰
Yeah. Yeah, John.

1536
01:36:36,124 --> 01:36:39,594
嗯，这里有传言
说你是个...骑马高手
Uh, there's a rumor around here that you're a... a horse guy.

1537
01:36:39,727 --> 01:36:41,396
是的，我曾为波士顿警局骑马
Yup, I rode for Boston PD.

1538
01:36:41,529 --> 01:36:44,132
实际上，我一直在骑马为什么问这个？
I've been riding my whole life, really. Why?

1539
01:36:44,266 --> 01:36:46,268
我们在加州的西部白宫
遇到了一些问题
We've been having some issues at the Western White House

1540
01:36:46,401 --> 01:36:48,270
- 在加州 - 什么样的问题？
- out in California. - What kind of issues?

1541
01:36:48,403 --> 01:36:49,437
没人会骑马
Nobody can ride.

1542
01:36:50,305 --> 01:36:53,241
是的，"生牛肉"不会说什么
但这挺尴尬的，
Yeah, Rawhide isn't gonna say anything but it's pretty embarrassing

1543
01:36:53,375 --> 01:36:55,844
当我们的人想奔跑时却只能牵着马走
when one of ours has to walk his horse when he wants to run.

1544
01:36:55,978 --> 01:36:57,079
你是说驰骋
You mean gallop.

1545
01:36:57,212 --> 01:36:58,146
是的随便了
Yeah. Whatever.

1546
01:36:59,281 --> 01:37:02,684
但是，呃，你想在我们出行时
负责那个细节吗？
But, uh, do you wanna head up that detail when we travel?

1547
01:37:05,453 --> 01:37:10,292
所以我会和...总统一起骑马？
So I'd be riding horses with the... with the President?

1548
01:37:11,226 --> 01:37:12,160
驾！
Giddyap.

1549
01:37:14,596 --> 01:37:16,331
- 好的 - 很好
- Okay. - All right.

1550
01:37:20,702 --> 01:37:23,571
与其他总统不同，
Unlike other presidents,

1551
01:37:23,738 --> 01:37:27,109
这位十字军战士并不急于与我们会面
The Crusader was in no rush to meet with us.

1552
01:37:28,143 --> 01:37:30,312
这造成了一个问题
This created a problem.

1553
01:37:35,951 --> 01:37:37,452
这是最新情况
Here's the latest.

1554
01:37:46,461 --> 01:37:47,462
这个，
This here,

1555
01:37:48,663 --> 01:37:49,731
这只是...
this is only...

1556
01:38:03,478 --> 01:38:06,081
如果他们不断死去,我怎么跟他们交谈呢?
How can I talk to them if they keep dying on me?

1557
01:38:11,519 --> 01:38:15,023
罗恩,我们正在急需能源
我们必须从某处获得它,
We are starving for energy, Ron, and we've got to get it somewhere

1558
01:38:15,157 --> 01:38:17,692
而且我们负担不起我们一直在支付的价格
and we can't afford what we've been paying.

1559
01:38:17,825 --> 01:38:19,827
但是从苏联购买?
But buying it from the Soviet Union?

1560
01:38:19,962 --> 01:38:24,699
你知道那笔钱直接用于
制造指向你的导弹
You know that that money is going directly into a missile pointed at you.

1561
01:38:24,832 --> 01:38:26,534
总统先生,
Mr. President,

1562
01:38:27,502 --> 01:38:29,337
给我一个替代方案
give me an alternative.

1563
01:38:29,471 --> 01:38:34,509
沙特已同意增加石油产量,
The Saudis have agreed to increase oil production,

1564
01:38:34,642 --> 01:38:37,879
只要我们从他们那里购买
而不是从俄罗斯
as long as we buy it from them, not the Russians.

1565
01:38:38,013 --> 01:38:41,416
如果我们能说服
我们的盟友与我们站在一起
And if we can get our friends to go along with us.

1566
01:38:41,549 --> 01:38:44,886
你能在国内推销这个吗?
对你的得克萨斯人?
And you can sell this at home? To your Texans?

1567
01:38:45,020 --> 01:38:47,555
这会使油价降到每桶不到10美元
It will drop oil to under ten dollars a barrel.

1568
01:38:47,689 --> 01:38:50,092
哦,我肯定会因此遭受政治打击
Oh, I'll take a political hit for it, that's for sure.

1569
01:38:50,225 --> 01:38:52,694
得克萨斯人喜欢赚钱
是的,他们确实如此
And Texans love to make money, yes, they do.

1570
01:38:52,827 --> 01:38:54,262
我们都喜欢
We all do.

1571
01:38:54,396 --> 01:38:56,564
但他们更爱自由
But they love their freedom even more.

1572
01:38:56,698 --> 01:39:01,603
先是邪恶帝国,现在又是这个
First, the Evil Empire and now this.

1573
01:39:01,736 --> 01:39:03,905
你似乎并不想交朋友
You're certainly not looking to make friends.

1574
01:39:04,039 --> 01:39:05,307
不,我不想
No, I'm not.

1575
01:39:05,440 --> 01:39:07,275
但也许你应该
But perhaps you should.

1576
01:39:07,409 --> 01:39:09,077
我见过他们的新人,戈尔巴乔夫
I met their new man, Gorbachev.

1577
01:39:09,211 --> 01:39:11,879
他是一个非常不同类型的俄罗斯人
He is a very different kind of Russian.

1578
01:39:12,014 --> 01:39:17,385
我告诉他
你是一个非常非常不同类型
And I told him you were a very, very different kind

1579
01:39:17,519 --> 01:39:19,121
的美国人
of an American.

1580
01:39:22,924 --> 01:39:25,760
- 提高征兵人数好的 - 啊!
- Pushing up the draft. All right. - Ah!

1581
01:39:25,893 --> 01:39:27,495
- 哦,哦,哦 - 嘿,嘿安静嘘!
- Ow! Oh, oh. - Hey, hey. Quiet. Shh!

1582
01:39:29,097 --> 01:39:31,399
晚上好里根总统今晚在日内瓦,
Good evening. President Reagan is in Geneva tonight

1583
01:39:31,566 --> 01:39:33,001
准备参加与戈尔巴乔夫的峰会
ready for the Gorbachev summit.

1584
01:39:35,703 --> 01:39:38,740
男爵很荣幸能在这个场合
The baron is honored to have you stay at his home

1585
01:39:38,873 --> 01:39:40,642
- 让您入住他的家 - 谢谢
- for this occasion. - Thank you.

1586
01:39:40,775 --> 01:39:42,677
请转达我们的感激之情
Please let him know how much we appreciate it.

1587
01:39:42,810 --> 01:39:46,648
呃...[笑] 金鱼
Uh... [chuckles] The goldfish.

1588
01:39:46,781 --> 01:39:50,352
似乎男爵的儿子非常喜欢它
It seems that the baron's son is very attached to it.

1589
01:39:50,485 --> 01:39:53,355
它每天需要喂食两次
It needs to be fed twice every day.

1590
01:39:53,488 --> 01:39:55,857
好的,我会亲自喂它的
Well, I will, uh, do it personally.

1591
01:39:59,094 --> 01:40:02,097
有些事情,你知道
我还是可以自己做的
There are a few things,I can do myself, you know?

1592
01:40:09,137 --> 01:40:11,206
- 他们到了 - 哦
-  They've arrived. - Oh.

1593
01:40:11,339 --> 01:40:13,308
哦，那么...好的
Oh, then... Yes.

1594
01:40:15,009 --> 01:40:16,311
我们开始吧
Here we go.

1595
01:40:16,444 --> 01:40:18,546
哦，不把外套脱掉
Oh, no. Coat off.

1596
01:40:18,680 --> 01:40:20,315
外面冷得要命
It's below freezing out there.

1597
01:40:20,448 --> 01:40:22,617
全世界都在关注这次会面，乔治
The whole world is watching this meeting, George.

1598
01:40:22,750 --> 01:40:25,720
他需要展现最佳状态
那件大衣不行
He needs to look his best, and that overcoat is not working.

1599
01:40:25,853 --> 01:40:27,455
好吧，你们负责政策，
Well, you guys are in charge of policy,

1600
01:40:27,589 --> 01:40:30,392
但即使是自由世界的领导人也有老板，
but even the leader of the free world has a boss,

1601
01:40:30,525 --> 01:40:33,961
而她负责形象呈现
and she's in charge of presentation.

1602
01:40:36,331 --> 01:40:38,266
在峰会开始之前，
And before the summit had begun,

1603
01:40:38,433 --> 01:40:41,803
我们发现自己已经处于劣势，
we found ourselves already at a disadvantage,

1604
01:40:41,969 --> 01:40:45,507
因为总统看起来比总书记更好
as the President looked better than the General Secretary.

1605
01:40:54,649 --> 01:40:57,552
让我一开始就说明
Let me state at the outset.

1606
01:40:57,685 --> 01:40:59,721
你不应该有任何幻想
You should have no illusions

1607
01:40:59,854 --> 01:41:01,856
认为你能使我们破产
that you can bankrupt us.

1608
01:41:02,023 --> 01:41:04,592
十字军从容应对...
The Crusader took it all in stride...

1609
01:41:04,759 --> 01:41:08,530
- 我们可以在陆地上与你匹敌...
- ...听出了其中的真意
- We can match you on land... - ...hearing it for what it was.

1610
01:41:08,663 --> 01:41:12,667
...以及空中和太空
...and air and space.

1611
01:41:14,936 --> 01:41:16,771
这是党的强制性表态
Mandatory messaging from the Party.

1612
01:41:19,907 --> 01:41:21,443
依我看，
As I see it,

1613
01:41:21,576 --> 01:41:26,080
我们不是因为武装而互不信任
we don't mistrust each other because we're armed.

1614
01:41:26,214 --> 01:41:28,015
我们武装
We're armed

1615
01:41:28,150 --> 01:41:30,685
是因为我们互不信任
because we mistrust each other.

1616
01:41:32,487 --> 01:41:36,057
但我认为我们都同意最重要的一点
But I think that we both agree on the most important thing.

1617
01:41:36,758 --> 01:41:40,428
核战争永远不可能赢
A nuclear war can never be won

1618
01:41:40,562 --> 01:41:42,864
也绝不能打
and must never be fought.

1619
01:41:46,534 --> 01:41:48,102
他确实模棱两可
He's definitely ambiguous.

1620
01:41:48,236 --> 01:41:50,572
这很清楚
没有任何模棱两可的地方
It's perfectly clear, there's nothing ambiguous about it.

1621
01:41:50,705 --> 01:41:52,774
你像往常一样占了上风
You come out ahead as you usually do.

1622
01:41:52,907 --> 01:41:56,311
一再违反盐巴 I和II条约
Violation after violation of SALT I and II.

1623
01:41:56,444 --> 01:41:59,781
违反？
这不过是你们在太空军事化而已
Violation? This is nothing more than you militarizing space.

1624
01:42:05,720 --> 01:42:10,158
我看到他脸上始终挂着温和的微笑
I saw a gentle smile that never left his face.

1625
01:42:11,293 --> 01:42:15,463
他很有魅力
但他仍然是那个狂热分子
He was disarming, but still he was the zealot

1626
01:42:15,630 --> 01:42:17,865
称我们为邪恶帝国的人
that called us an Evil Empire.

1627
01:42:18,032 --> 01:42:20,335
我们不能放松警惕
And we could not let our guard down.

1628
01:42:20,468 --> 01:42:23,771
你知道，我过去常常演戏
You know, I used to do a little acting

1629
01:42:23,905 --> 01:42:26,341
大约二百年前在好莱坞
a couple hundred years ago back in Hollywood.

1630
01:42:26,474 --> 01:42:29,010
让我给你展示
我们过去如何处理这种情况
Let me show you how we used to handle this sort of thing.

1631
01:42:37,785 --> 01:42:38,753
第二次拍摄
Take two.

1632
01:42:41,823 --> 01:42:44,025
你好，米哈伊尔我叫罗恩
Hello, Mikhail. My name's Ron.

1633
01:42:48,663 --> 01:42:50,665
你想出去散散步吗？
How would you like to go for a little walk?

1634
01:43:04,279 --> 01:43:06,214
他们说您，总统先生，
What they say about you, Mr. President,

1635
01:43:06,348 --> 01:43:09,484
"他掏空你的口袋
还让你感觉良好"
"He picks your pocket and makes you feel good about it."

1636
01:43:09,617 --> 01:43:13,721
嗯，我以前听过
更糟的评价，糟糕多了
Well, I've had much worse said about me before, way worse.

1637
01:43:13,855 --> 01:43:16,324
我也是这是我们工作的风险
As have I. Hazard of our job.

1638
01:43:18,660 --> 01:43:20,127
我想让您知道
I want to let you know

1639
01:43:21,028 --> 01:43:23,698
我们追求的是同一件事，米哈伊尔
that we seek the same thing, Mikhail.

1640
01:43:24,699 --> 01:43:26,033
是吗，罗恩？
Do we, Ron?

1641
01:43:27,001 --> 01:43:29,237
我们不是因为必须才来这里的
We are not here because we need to be.

1642
01:43:29,371 --> 01:43:32,006
我们渴望和平，就像您一样
We desire peace, just as you do.

1643
01:43:32,874 --> 01:43:36,177
但您的提议并不那么简单
But your proposal is not so simple.

1644
01:43:36,311 --> 01:43:39,514
哦，事实上，它很简单
Oh, actually, it is very simple.

1645
01:43:40,882 --> 01:43:42,183
只是不容易
It's just not easy.

1646
01:43:43,818 --> 01:43:48,356
但我相信您和我，我们能做到
But I believe that you and I, we can do it.

1647
01:43:48,490 --> 01:43:50,258
事实上，我们必须做到
In fact, we must.

1648
01:43:51,125 --> 01:43:52,427
世界要求我们这么做
The world demands it.

1649
01:43:52,560 --> 01:43:54,596
毕竟，这不就是我们
为之工作的对象吗？
And after all, isn't that who we work for?

1650
01:43:54,729 --> 01:43:57,332
人民和上帝
The people and the man upstairs.

1651
01:43:57,465 --> 01:44:00,167
啊上帝
Ah. The man upstairs.

1652
01:44:01,403 --> 01:44:04,071
我祖母是个虔诚的基督徒，
My grandmother was a Christian woman,

1653
01:44:04,205 --> 01:44:06,173
每天都去教堂
go to church every day.

1654
01:44:06,308 --> 01:44:07,909
之后她会说，
And after, would say,

1655
01:44:08,042 --> 01:44:10,445
"米哈伊尔，我今天去了教堂
"Mikhail, I went to church today.

1656
01:44:10,578 --> 01:44:12,847
我为无神论者祈祷了
I prayed for the atheist.

1657
01:44:12,980 --> 01:44:14,916
我为你祈祷了"
I prayed for you."

1658
01:44:15,049 --> 01:44:18,420
嗯，我想您的祖母和我的母亲
Well, I think that your grandmother and my mother

1659
01:44:18,553 --> 01:44:20,355
本可以成为很好的朋友
could have been very good friends.

1660
01:44:22,089 --> 01:44:23,558
所以您就是那个老虎人
So you're the Tiger Man.

1661
01:44:23,691 --> 01:44:25,893
对不起？老虎人？
Excuse me? Tiger Man?

1662
01:44:26,027 --> 01:44:28,696
我很喜欢美国棒球
I like American baseball, very much.

1663
01:44:28,830 --> 01:44:30,231
哦，是吗？您最喜欢哪支队伍？
Oh, yeah? Who's your favorite team?

1664
01:44:30,365 --> 01:44:32,400
纽约扬基队您呢？
New York Yankees. And you?

1665
01:44:32,534 --> 01:44:34,569
呃，圣路易斯红雀队
Uh, St. Louis Cardinals.

1666
01:44:35,603 --> 01:44:38,072
世界大赛第7场
Game 7, World Series.

1667
01:44:38,205 --> 01:44:41,576
很抱歉，但是什么系列赛？
Very sorry, but what series?

1668
01:44:41,709 --> 01:44:44,379
哦，下次您来美国时
我会确保您能看场比赛
Oh, next time you're in the States, I'll make sure you get to a game.

1669
01:44:46,448 --> 01:44:48,583
不，不，不 让他们谈
No, no, no, no. Let them talk.

1670
01:44:48,716 --> 01:44:50,552
你要是进去就被解雇了
You go in there, you're fired.

1671
01:44:54,088 --> 01:44:55,156
老虎人
Tiger Man.

1672
01:44:56,290 --> 01:44:57,792
我的提议是这样的
My proposal...

1673
01:44:59,060 --> 01:44:59,994
就是这个
is this.

1674
01:45:00,795 --> 01:45:02,630
您和我，
That you and I,

1675
01:45:02,764 --> 01:45:05,767
在我离任之前，
by the time that I leave office,

1676
01:45:05,900 --> 01:45:10,137
能将我们的导弹数量减少一半
can reduce our missile counts by half.

1677
01:45:11,439 --> 01:45:12,340
嗯
Hmm.

1678
01:45:14,275 --> 01:45:16,444
我也不是一个有耐心的人
I'm not a patient man either.

1679
01:45:17,879 --> 01:45:20,582
我不打算在他们完全消失之前
I do not intend to leave office

1680
01:45:20,715 --> 01:45:22,149
离开办公室，
before they are gone,

1681
01:45:22,984 --> 01:45:23,985
彻底消失
completely.

1682
01:45:39,734 --> 01:45:40,968
哦，不
Oh, no.

1683
01:45:41,102 --> 01:45:42,937
亲爱的，看我做了什么
Honey, look what I've done.

1684
01:45:43,070 --> 01:45:44,305
哦，天哪
Oh, dear.

1685
01:45:44,439 --> 01:45:45,940
也许我们可以找到另一条
Maybe we can find another one.

1686
01:45:46,073 --> 01:45:48,876
呃，总统先生
我们还有五分钟就要直播了
Uh, Mr. President, we-we go live in five-five minutes.

1687
01:45:49,010 --> 01:45:50,878
哦，我-我觉得我们应该找另一条
Oh, I-I think we should find another one.

1688
01:45:51,012 --> 01:45:52,179
哦，不！
Oh, no!

1689
01:45:52,313 --> 01:45:54,348
每个孩子都认识自己的金鱼
Every kid knows his goldfish.

1690
01:45:54,482 --> 01:45:55,817
我要给他写张便条
I'm gonna write him a note.

1691
01:45:55,950 --> 01:45:57,351
我-我们现在需要走了
W-we need to go now.

1692
01:45:57,485 --> 01:45:59,821
我是说，全世界都在等着
I mean, the entire world is waiting.

1693
01:45:59,954 --> 01:46:01,689
世界可以等
The world can wait.

1694
01:46:01,823 --> 01:46:04,291
我要给他写张便条
I'm going to write him a note.

1695
01:46:04,426 --> 01:46:08,496
- 南希... - 这就是我的罗尼
-  Nancy... - That's my Ronnie.

1696
01:46:08,663 --> 01:46:12,033
- 我们必须等待
- 除了同意再次会面外，
- We have to wait. -  Nothing was really agreed to yet

1697
01:46:12,199 --> 01:46:13,968
实际上还没有达成任何协议
beyond agreeing to meet again.

1698
01:46:14,135 --> 01:46:18,039
但是苏联和美国正在互相交谈，
But the Soviet Union and USA were talking to one another

1699
01:46:18,205 --> 01:46:20,374
而不是互相对抗
instead of at one another.

1700
01:46:33,855 --> 01:46:38,025
里根对抗我们的盟友包括教皇、
Reagan's allies against us included the Pope,

1701
01:46:38,192 --> 01:46:40,462
铁娘子撒切尔、
Thatcher, the Iron Lady,

1702
01:46:40,628 --> 01:46:45,166
以及西德和日本的领导人
科尔和中曾根
and leaders of West Germany and Japan, Cole and Nakasone.

1703
01:46:45,299 --> 01:46:47,234
我们坚定地支持你
We stand firmly behind you.

1704
01:46:48,536 --> 01:46:50,905
当你与戈尔巴乔夫秘书谈话时，
When you speak with Secretary Gorbachev,

1705
01:46:52,474 --> 01:46:55,276
你就是在为自由世界的我们发声
you are speaking for us in free world.

1706
01:46:55,443 --> 01:46:56,744
好吧，我们明白
Well, we understand

1707
01:46:56,878 --> 01:46:59,714
你被共产主义者包围着，
that you are surrounded by communists,

1708
01:46:59,847 --> 01:47:02,383
我们感谢你站在我们这边
and we appreciate you standing with us.

1709
01:47:02,550 --> 01:47:04,652
要小心记住，
Be careful. Remember,

1710
01:47:04,819 --> 01:47:09,223
共产主义者
为了达到目的不惜说谎
communists have no problem with lying to achieve their goals.

1711
01:47:09,356 --> 01:47:12,927
他们在测试你
看你是否会坚定立场
They are testing you to see if you will stand firm.

1712
01:47:13,094 --> 01:47:16,263
别担心我在好莱坞
就和这些家伙打过交道
Don't worry. I dealt with these guys back in Hollywood.

1713
01:47:16,430 --> 01:47:18,633
我背上甚至还有伤疤可以证明
I even have the scars on my back to prove it.

1714
01:47:18,766 --> 01:47:20,267
我向你保证，
And I promise you,

1715
01:47:21,368 --> 01:47:22,870
我们不会输的
we're not going to lose.

1716
01:47:24,572 --> 01:47:28,075
其他新闻
里根总统已经抵达冰岛雷克雅未克，
In other news, President Reagan has landed in Reykjavík, Iceland

1717
01:47:28,242 --> 01:47:32,079
继续与苏联总理戈尔巴乔夫
就核裁军问题进行讨论
to continue discussions with Soviet Premier Gorbachev over nuclear disarmament.

1718
01:47:33,380 --> 01:47:36,083
全面削减百分之五十
Fifty percent across the board reduction.

1719
01:47:36,217 --> 01:47:40,988
所有武器组别,战术武器
中程核武器、洲际弹道导弹
All weapons groups, tactical, INF, ICBM.

1720
01:47:41,122 --> 01:47:45,226
作为交换
暂停你们的战略防御计划
In exchange, suspension of your Strategic,Defense Initiative.

1721
01:47:45,359 --> 01:47:48,229
有人称之为"星球大战"
"Star Wars," some refer to it.

1722
01:47:50,532 --> 01:47:51,666
反提议
Counter proposal.

1723
01:47:53,568 --> 01:47:57,438
我们分享所有战略防御计划技术,
We share all SDI technology,

1724
01:47:58,405 --> 01:47:59,807
我们共同开发,
we develop it together,

1725
01:48:00,642 --> 01:48:02,510
我们甚至愿意承担费用
we'll even pay for it.

1726
01:48:02,644 --> 01:48:06,514
我们在十年内消除所有弹道导弹,
And we eliminate all ballistic missiles

1727
01:48:06,648 --> 01:48:09,183
共同完成
in ten years. Together.

1728
01:48:09,316 --> 01:48:12,654
你们拒绝分享石油钻探技术,
You refuse to share oil-drilling technology

1729
01:48:12,787 --> 01:48:14,288
却提出这个建议?
and you offer this?

1730
01:48:14,421 --> 01:48:19,160
战略防御计划是一个完全防御性的系统
SDI is a completely defensive system.

1731
01:48:22,296 --> 01:48:24,265
这就是底线,总统先生
This is the line, Mr. President.

1732
01:48:25,299 --> 01:48:26,534
如果你离开,
If you walk away,

1733
01:48:27,434 --> 01:48:29,804
你将错过成为历史上
you will have missed the chance of going down in history

1734
01:48:29,937 --> 01:48:33,875
为核裁军铺平道路的总统的机会
as the president who paved the way for nuclear disarmament.

1735
01:48:34,008 --> 01:48:37,812
你将如何向你的
"自由人民"解释这一点?
How will you explain this to your "free people?"

1736
01:48:39,480 --> 01:48:40,948
总统先生,
Mr. President,

1737
01:48:41,082 --> 01:48:45,019
我正在给你提供你总统任期内最大的胜利
I'm offering you the biggest win of your presidency.

1738
01:48:46,988 --> 01:48:49,056
只要放弃战略防御计划
Just drop SDI.

1739
01:49:13,881 --> 01:49:14,849
不
Nyet.

1740
01:49:18,886 --> 01:49:20,254
我们走吧,乔治
Let's go, George.

1741
01:49:28,329 --> 01:49:31,065
你会为这一件事失去整个协议?
You would lose the whole deal over this one thing?

1742
01:49:31,198 --> 01:49:32,566
这是一个公平的提议
This is a fair offer.

1743
01:49:33,901 --> 01:49:35,603
我的提议也是
As was mine.

1744
01:49:35,737 --> 01:49:37,705
我不知道我还能做什么
I don't know what more,I could have done.

1745
01:49:40,474 --> 01:49:42,076
你本可以说yes的
You could have said yes.

1746
01:49:46,347 --> 01:49:49,383
在他离开谈判桌后,
After he walked away from the negotiating table,

1747
01:49:49,550 --> 01:49:52,153
我们处于一个非常黑暗的境地
we were in a very dark place.

1748
01:49:52,319 --> 01:49:54,055
我们知道一切都结束了,
We knew it was over,

1749
01:49:54,221 --> 01:49:56,891
除非发生一些非凡的事情
unless something extraordinary happened.

1750
01:50:00,561 --> 01:50:04,598
我们又截获了
两批从古巴运往尼加拉瓜的
We've intercepted two more shipments of Soviet RPGs and AK-47s

1751
01:50:04,732 --> 01:50:07,101
苏联火箭筒和AK-47步枪
coming out of Cuba, headed for Nicaragua.

1752
01:50:07,935 --> 01:50:10,271
自由战士们躲在山里
The freedom fighters are holed up in the mountains.

1753
01:50:10,404 --> 01:50:12,774
这是大卫对抗歌利亚,但他们在努力坚持
It's David and Goliath, but they're making a go of it.

1754
01:50:13,941 --> 01:50:15,542
嗯,我喜欢这些家伙
Well, I like these guys.

1755
01:50:15,677 --> 01:50:19,046
他们让我想起华盛顿和大陆军
They remind me of Washington and the Continental Army.

1756
01:50:19,180 --> 01:50:20,547
他们需要什么?
What do they need?

1757
01:50:20,682 --> 01:50:22,449
他们一直需要什么?
What do they always need?

1758
01:50:22,583 --> 01:50:24,218
绷带、枪支和钱
Band-Aids, guns, and money.

1759
01:50:25,352 --> 01:50:27,254
好,给他们想要的
Well, give them what they want.

1760
01:50:27,388 --> 01:50:31,092
总统先生,在这件事上
我们不会得到国会的支持
Mr. President, we won't have the Congress with us on this one.

1761
01:50:40,802 --> 01:50:43,237
除了真相,别无其他
你愿意以上帝的名义发誓吗?
And nothing but the truth, so help you God?

1762
01:50:43,404 --> 01:50:44,672
- 我愿意 - 请坐
- I do. - Please be seated.

1763
01:50:45,773 --> 01:50:47,975
美国国会已经说了不
The American Congress had said no

1764
01:50:48,142 --> 01:50:51,112
不给他在尼加拉瓜的朋友们钱
to giving money to his friends in Nicaragua.

1765
01:50:51,278 --> 01:50:54,648
而"十字军"在中东有人质
And The Crusader had hostages in the Middle East

1766
01:50:54,816 --> 01:50:56,617
需要解救他们
and needed to free them.

1767
01:50:56,784 --> 01:51:01,889
但美国的政策是
永远不与恐怖分子谈判
But it was American policy never to negotiate with terrorists.

1768
01:51:02,056 --> 01:51:05,326
但在某处,一个计划诞生了
But somewhere, a plan was hatched.

1769
01:51:10,765 --> 01:51:15,036
里根的伊朗门事件归结为这一点
Reagan's Iran-Contra situation comes down to this.

1770
01:51:15,169 --> 01:51:17,772
总统知道什么,他什么时候知道的?
What did the president know, and when did he know it?

1771
01:51:17,905 --> 01:51:21,342
如果你们这些媒体人想要更多答案,
And if you, people of the press, want any more answers,

1772
01:51:21,475 --> 01:51:23,477
去问里根总统吧
you ask President Reagan.

1773
01:51:23,644 --> 01:51:26,347
他与我们斗争了五十年
Five decades of his struggle against us

1774
01:51:26,513 --> 01:51:31,485
最终归结为他能否在国内丑闻中幸存
and it came down to whether he could survive a domestic scandal.

1775
01:51:31,618 --> 01:51:35,522
尽管有各种wildly推测和虚假报道,
In spite of the wildly speculative and false reports,

1776
01:51:35,656 --> 01:51:39,193
我们不与恐怖分子谈判
we do not negotiate with terrorists

1777
01:51:39,326 --> 01:51:41,628
我们也没有用武器
and we did not trade arms

1778
01:51:41,763 --> 01:51:44,065
换取人质
for hostages.

1779
01:51:44,231 --> 01:51:46,934
这些指控可能构成弹劾罪
These accusations are potentially impeachable offenses.

1780
01:51:47,101 --> 01:51:50,204
如果属实,一些观察家认为他的总统任期
And if true, some observers believe his presidency

1781
01:51:50,371 --> 01:51:51,873
可能岌岌可危
could be hanging in the balance.

1782
01:51:52,039 --> 01:51:54,876
白宫W新闻4台记者卡尔·朗报道
For W News 4 at the White House, I'm Carl Long.

1783
01:52:05,386 --> 01:52:08,255
罗尼,你必须做点什么
Ronnie, you have to do something.

1784
01:52:09,156 --> 01:52:10,157
你看到这个了吗?
Have you seen this?

1785
01:52:11,358 --> 01:52:12,726
是的,我看到了
Yes, I've seen it.

1786
01:52:12,860 --> 01:52:14,528
你有在听这些人说话吗?
Are you listening to these people?

1787
01:52:15,362 --> 01:52:18,099
他们只想看到你倒台
They want nothing more than to see you burn.

1788
01:52:18,232 --> 01:52:21,836
你知道,他们可能笑着
叫你"总统先生",但他们恨你
You know, they may smile and call you "Mr. President," but they hate you.

1789
01:52:21,969 --> 01:52:24,872
他们恨你说的话
恨你的信仰,恨你这个人
They hate what you say, what you believe in, who you are.

1790
01:52:25,006 --> 01:52:26,740
亲爱的,我就是不能接受这一点
Honey, I just can't accept that.

1791
01:52:26,874 --> 01:52:29,576
不,不,你从来都不能
No, no, you never could.

1792
01:52:29,710 --> 01:52:32,679
你是乐观主义者
你总是想看到人性中的善
You're the optimist. You're the one who wants to see the good in people.

1793
01:52:32,814 --> 01:52:35,850
但我的工作就是看穿他们,保护你
But it's my job to see through them and protect you.

1794
01:52:35,983 --> 01:52:39,053
嗯,这就是为什么我们是如此好的搭档
Well, that's why we're such a good team.

1795
01:52:41,488 --> 01:52:45,459
亲爱的,你了解华盛顿
你知道它是如何运作的
Honey, you know Washington. You know the way it works.

1796
01:52:45,592 --> 01:52:48,429
- 这只是政治,仅此而已
- 罗尼,他们在谈弹劾!
- It's politics, that's all. - Ronnie, they're talking impeachment!

1797
01:52:48,562 --> 01:52:52,599
- 不会被弹劾的
- 是的,他们想毁掉你!
- No impeachment. - Yes, they wanna destroy you!

1798
01:52:52,733 --> 01:52:55,803
他们要对你进行审判，把你赶下台！
They're putting you on trial, removing you from office!

1799
01:52:55,937 --> 01:52:57,805
这已经不是政治问题了
This isn't about politics anymore.

1800
01:52:57,939 --> 01:52:59,240
这关系到你自己
This is about you.

1801
01:53:00,241 --> 01:53:03,244
一切都岌岌可危再来一个头条新闻，
Everything is at stake. One more headline,

1802
01:53:03,377 --> 01:53:06,113
再来一个重要证人
再来一次逮捕，他们就会这么做
one more star witness, one more arrest, and they will do it.

1803
01:53:06,247 --> 01:53:08,549
我已经与他们合作了
I have cooperated with them.

1804
01:53:08,682 --> 01:53:10,717
我任命了一名特别检察官
I appointed a special prosecutor.

1805
01:53:10,852 --> 01:53:13,754
我已经交出了所有我有的文件
I've turned over every document I have.

1806
01:53:13,888 --> 01:53:15,622
你还要我怎么做？
What would you have me do?

1807
01:53:15,756 --> 01:53:17,491
我要你战斗，
I want you to fight

1808
01:53:17,624 --> 01:53:19,460
否则这一切就结束了！
or this is all over!

1809
01:53:30,537 --> 01:53:32,106
你可以雇人来做
You could always hire someone.

1810
01:53:32,239 --> 01:53:33,140
哈！
Ha!

1811
01:53:33,941 --> 01:53:36,510
怎么，你在找工作吗？
Why, you looking for work?

1812
01:53:36,643 --> 01:53:38,179
我有份工作给你，
I got a job for you

1813
01:53:39,313 --> 01:53:40,915
在华盛顿
back in Washington.

1814
01:53:41,048 --> 01:53:44,018
你是总统
你随时可以命令我回去
You're the president. You could always order me back there.

1815
01:53:46,087 --> 01:53:48,589
他们会弹劾我吗，比尔？
Are they gonna impeach me, Bill?

1816
01:53:48,722 --> 01:53:51,325
嗯，事情正朝那个方向发展，先生
Well, it's moving in that direction, sir.

1817
01:53:53,827 --> 01:53:55,963
总统先生，你是我的朋友
Mr. President, you're my friend.

1818
01:53:56,097 --> 01:53:58,332
我只能直白地跟你说
I can only speak to you straight.

1819
01:53:58,465 --> 01:54:01,002
肯定有一些法律被违反了，
Some laws got broken, for sure,

1820
01:54:01,135 --> 01:54:04,205
不管是你违反的还是别人违反的
whether you broke them or somebody else did.

1821
01:54:04,338 --> 01:54:07,641
所以现在你保持沉默并聘请律师
So now you're clamming up and lawyering up.

1822
01:54:07,774 --> 01:54:09,343
这是错误的做法
It's the wrong move.

1823
01:54:09,476 --> 01:54:11,645
这让每个人都感到困惑
甚至是那些爱你的人
It confuses everybody, even the ones that love you.

1824
01:54:13,247 --> 01:54:14,781
人们在想，也许你是...
People are thinking that maybe you're...

1825
01:54:14,916 --> 01:54:16,283
我失去理智了？是的
I'm losing it? Yeah.

1826
01:54:17,651 --> 01:54:18,685
我听说了
I've heard it.

1827
01:54:23,257 --> 01:54:26,027
你认为我应该怎么做，法官？
What do you think,I should do, Judge?

1828
01:54:26,160 --> 01:54:27,661
做你最擅长的事
What you do best.

1829
01:54:27,794 --> 01:54:28,996
告诉他们真相
Tell 'em the truth.

1830
01:54:52,286 --> 01:54:54,888
几个月前，我向美国人民宣称
A few months ago, I told the American people

1831
01:54:55,022 --> 01:54:57,824
我没有以武器换取人质
that I did not trade arms for hostages.

1832
01:54:57,959 --> 01:55:01,895
我的内心和最好的意图
仍然告诉我这是真的，
My heart and my best intentions still tell me that's true

1833
01:55:02,029 --> 01:55:05,899
但事实和证据告诉我并非如此
but the facts and the evidence tell me it is not.

1834
01:55:06,033 --> 01:55:10,237
现在，当你犯错时应该这样做
Now, what should happen when you make a mistake is this.

1835
01:55:10,371 --> 01:55:13,740
你承受批评
你把事情放在正确的角度，
You take your knocks, you put things in perspective,

1836
01:55:13,874 --> 01:55:16,077
你集中你的精力，
you pull your energies together,

1837
01:55:16,210 --> 01:55:19,113
你做出改变，然后继续前进
you make changes, and you go forward.

1838
01:55:19,981 --> 01:55:21,182
美国人
Americans.

1839
01:55:21,315 --> 01:55:23,184
你做错了事，你就要付出代价
You do them wrong, you'll pay for it.

1840
01:55:23,850 --> 01:55:28,022
但要看着他们的眼睛
承认你犯了错误，
But look them in the eye, admit you made a mistake,

1841
01:55:28,155 --> 01:55:30,224
他们每次都会原谅你
they forgive you every time.

1842
01:55:45,239 --> 01:55:46,974
他是总统
He was president.

1843
01:55:47,108 --> 01:55:48,809
他必须知道
He had to know.

1844
01:55:51,445 --> 01:55:54,381
他仍然是那个救生员
He was still the lifeguard.

1845
01:55:54,515 --> 01:55:56,783
他要把他的人民带回家
He was going to get his people home.

1846
01:56:01,222 --> 01:56:05,059
罗恩,我对你不太满意
让我们开门见山地说吧
I'm not pleased with you, Ron. Let's just get that said right up front.

1847
01:56:06,060 --> 01:56:08,229
嗯,我想不出我哪里惹你生气了
玛格丽特
Well, I can't imagine how I've upset you, Margaret.

1848
01:56:08,362 --> 01:56:10,564
我们又要讨论格林纳达的事吗?
Are we gonna go over Grenada again?

1849
01:56:10,697 --> 01:56:13,134
好吧,你当然不能逃避
Well, you're certainly not walking away

1850
01:56:13,267 --> 01:56:15,636
雷克雅未克发生的事...
from what happened at Reykjavík...

1851
01:56:15,769 --> 01:56:17,904
- 不 - 看来你在挑起争端
- No. - Looks like you're picking a fight.

1852
01:56:18,039 --> 01:56:21,108
不,但我不怕争端
No, but I'm not afraid of one.

1853
01:56:21,242 --> 01:56:24,645
也许这就是为什么密特朗称你为
Perhaps that is why,Mitterrand calls you

1854
01:56:24,778 --> 01:56:27,248
"危险的牛仔"
a "dangerous cowboy."

1855
01:56:28,415 --> 01:56:29,316
嗯,
Well,

1856
01:56:30,284 --> 01:56:32,853
至少我有
玛格丽特·撒切尔站在我这边
at least I have,Margaret Thatcher on my side.

1857
01:56:38,492 --> 01:56:40,794
- 他想说出来
- 他确实想,但我们永远无法说服舒尔茨
- He wants to say it. - He does, but we'll never get it past Shultz.

1858
01:56:40,927 --> 01:56:43,330
我是说
这是他们最不想让他谈论的事
I mean, it's the one thing they don't want him talking about.

1859
01:56:43,464 --> 01:56:45,132
我在德国的家人都在谈论这个
My family in Germany is talking about it.

1860
01:56:45,266 --> 01:56:47,468
每个人都在谈论他需要谈论这个
Everybody is talking about it. He needs to talk about it.

1861
01:56:47,601 --> 01:56:49,703
他要去戴维营,然后回到这里待一天,
He's going to Camp David, then he's back here for a day,

1862
01:56:49,836 --> 01:56:53,940
之后他要去欧洲
我们只有一次机会让他说这个
then he's going to Europe. We have one shot to have him say this.

1863
01:56:54,075 --> 01:56:55,542
现在或永远不可能
It's now or never.

1864
01:57:09,490 --> 01:57:11,658
嘿,把这个给我!我-我来拿谢谢
Hey, give me this! I-I'll take that. Thank you.

1865
01:57:13,360 --> 01:57:14,961
总统先生,一些轻松的读物
Mr. President, some light reading.

1866
01:57:16,530 --> 01:57:17,798
嘘!
Shh!

1867
01:57:23,437 --> 01:57:24,638
下午好
Good afternoon.

1868
01:57:27,441 --> 01:57:30,377
你们好,伙计们,今天是个适合飞行的好日子
Hello, fellas, good day to fly.

1869
01:57:30,511 --> 01:57:31,912
不过别来桶滚
No barrel rolls though.

1870
01:58:11,752 --> 01:58:13,887
嗯,我想那其实是第一夫人的问题
Well, I think that's a First Lady question, actually.

1871
01:58:14,020 --> 01:58:16,890
你为什么要这样对戈尔巴乔夫?
Why would you do this to Gorbachev?

1872
01:58:17,023 --> 01:58:19,426
你知道我们花了多长时间才达到这一步
You know how long it's taken us to get to this.

1873
01:58:19,560 --> 01:58:21,061
他们已经坐到谈判桌前了
他们准备达成协议,
They're at the table. They're ready to make a deal

1874
01:58:21,195 --> 01:58:22,796
而你想让他难堪?
and you wanna embarrass him?

1875
01:58:22,929 --> 01:58:25,732
戈尔巴乔夫是70年来
我们在那边的第一个朋友!
Gorbachev's the first friend we've had over there in 70 years!

1876
01:58:25,866 --> 01:58:28,101
你不能说这个
You can't say this.

1877
01:58:28,235 --> 01:58:30,804
我-我恳求你听我说
I'm-I'm begging you to listen to me.

1878
01:58:30,937 --> 01:58:34,308
你知道,当战略防御计划
被嘲笑时我支持了你
You know, I stood by you with SDI when it was ridiculed.

1879
01:58:34,441 --> 01:58:36,310
我支持你对付尼加拉瓜反政府武装
I supported you with the Contras.

1880
01:58:36,443 --> 01:58:39,413
我甚至在雷克雅未克会谈上
弄得灰头土脸
I even walked out of Reykjavík with egg on my face.

1881
01:58:39,546 --> 01:58:42,283
但这次太过分了
But this goes too far.

1882
01:58:42,416 --> 01:58:44,218
这比"邪恶帝国"还要糟糕
This is worse than Evil Empire.

1883
01:58:44,351 --> 01:58:47,488
你要炸毁日内瓦
你要毁掉八年的外交努力
You're gonna blow up Geneva, you blow up eight years of diplomacy.

1884
01:58:47,621 --> 01:58:50,090
我们会回到原点，甚至更糟！
We'll be right back where we started from, or worse!

1885
01:58:53,394 --> 01:58:55,662
"清晰就是力量"
"Clarity is power."

1886
01:58:55,796 --> 01:58:58,965
你知道，一位伟人曾对我说过这句话
You know, a very great man once said that to me.

1887
01:59:00,434 --> 01:59:02,269
乔治，我们来这里是为了什么...
What are we here for, George...

1888
01:59:03,970 --> 01:59:05,138
不就是为了赢吗？
but to win?

1889
01:59:13,414 --> 01:59:16,116
在我身后矗立着一堵墙
Behind me stands a wall.

1890
01:59:16,950 --> 01:59:19,786
它是一个庞大屏障系统的一部分，
Part of a vast system of barriers

1891
01:59:19,920 --> 01:59:22,789
将整个欧洲大陆一分为二
that divide the entire continent of Europe.

1892
01:59:22,923 --> 01:59:27,428
一道由铁丝网、混凝土、
A gash of barbed wire, concrete,

1893
01:59:27,561 --> 01:59:30,431
警犬和哨塔组成的伤痕，
dogs, and guard towers,

1894
01:59:30,564 --> 01:59:34,535
强加了极权国家的意志
imposing the will of a totalitarian state.

1895
01:59:35,569 --> 01:59:37,704
只要这扇大门还关着，
As long as this gate is closed

1896
01:59:37,838 --> 01:59:40,674
只要这道伤疤还被允许存在，
and this scar is permitted to stand,

1897
01:59:40,807 --> 01:59:45,111
全人类的自由就仍是个问题
there is a question of freedom for all mankind.

1898
01:59:53,487 --> 01:59:56,923
极权主义世界产生落后，
The totalitarian world produces backwardness

1899
01:59:57,090 --> 02:00:01,262
因为它对精神造成了如此大的伤害
because it does such violence to the spirit.

1900
02:00:01,428 --> 02:00:06,833
阻碍了人类创造
享受甚至崇拜的冲动
Thwarting the human impulse to create, to enjoy, even to worship.

1901
02:00:07,768 --> 02:00:11,238
在这里，在柏林
就像这座城市本身一样，
Here in Berlin, like the city itself,

1902
02:00:11,372 --> 02:00:15,175
爱的象征，崇拜的象征
symbols of love, symbols of worship

1903
02:00:15,309 --> 02:00:17,311
是无法被压制的
cannot be suppressed.

1904
02:00:24,885 --> 02:00:28,855
苏联可以做出一个标志，
There is one sign that the Soviets can make,

1905
02:00:28,989 --> 02:00:33,159
这个标志将明确且戏剧性地推进
that would unmistakably and dramatically advance

1906
02:00:33,294 --> 02:00:35,529
自由与和平的事业
the cause of freedom and peace.

1907
02:00:36,630 --> 02:00:38,799
戈尔巴乔夫总书记，
General Secretary Gorbachev,

1908
02:00:38,965 --> 02:00:41,167
如果你寻求和平，
if you seek peace,

1909
02:00:41,335 --> 02:00:44,671
如果你寻求自由化和变革，
if you seek liberalization and change,

1910
02:00:44,838 --> 02:00:47,107
就来到这扇门前吧
come here to this gate.

1911
02:00:49,476 --> 02:00:51,745
戈尔巴乔夫先生，
Mr. Gorbachev,

1912
02:00:51,878 --> 02:00:53,614
打开这扇门
open this gate.

1913
02:00:55,181 --> 02:00:56,517
他会说出那句话吗？
Is he gonna say it?

1914
02:01:02,356 --> 02:01:04,525
戈尔巴乔夫先生，
Mr. Gorbachev,

1915
02:01:04,658 --> 02:01:07,060
推倒这堵墙
tear down this wall.

1916
02:01:13,033 --> 02:01:14,768
喔！
Whoo!

1917
02:01:14,901 --> 02:01:17,704
喔！
Whoo!

1918
02:01:27,448 --> 02:01:29,416
干得好，牛仔
Well done, cowboy.

1919
02:02:08,288 --> 02:02:10,090
在冷战的棋局中，
In the chess game of the Cold War,

1920
02:02:11,592 --> 02:02:12,993
这是将军
it was checkmate.

1921
02:02:21,968 --> 02:02:23,770
难以想象的事情
The unimaginable is happening

1922
02:02:23,937 --> 02:02:25,772
正在柏林发生
right now in Berlin.

1923
02:02:25,939 --> 02:02:27,307
令人震惊的事态发展在一夜之间发生
Shocking developments overnight

1924
02:02:27,474 --> 02:02:28,975
东德宣布其公民
as East Germany announced its citizens

1925
02:02:29,142 --> 02:02:31,277
可以自由前往西德
can travel freely to West Germany.

1926
02:02:31,445 --> 02:02:34,114
没人认为可能发生的事情
What no one thought could happen

1927
02:02:34,280 --> 02:02:36,049
此刻正在发生
is happening right now.

1928
02:03:04,611 --> 02:03:07,514
几小时内，城市爆发了庆祝活动
Within hours, the city erupted in celebration

1929
02:03:07,681 --> 02:03:10,116
东德和西德人民
用锤子敲打分隔他们30年的墙壁
as East and West Germans took hammers to the wall

1930
02:03:10,283 --> 02:03:12,419
这堵墙已经将他们分隔了30年
that had separated them for 30 years.

1931
02:03:22,696 --> 02:03:26,032
柏林墙倒塌两年后，
Two years, after the wall fell,

1932
02:03:26,199 --> 02:03:28,168
苏联不复存在
the Soviet Union was no more.

1933
02:03:31,805 --> 02:03:33,874
我知道他就是那个人
I knew he was the one.

1934
02:03:35,476 --> 02:03:38,679
他就是那个会让我们垮台的人
He was the one who would bring us down.

1935
02:03:38,812 --> 02:03:43,049
不是用导弹或枪支，甚至不是用政治
Not with missiles or guns or even politics.

1936
02:03:43,183 --> 02:03:44,885
而是用更伟大的东西
Something much greater.

1937
02:03:51,191 --> 02:03:54,695
人们不会为权力献出生命，
People will not give their lives for power,

1938
02:03:54,828 --> 02:03:57,598
也不会为国家，甚至不会为意识形态
or a State, or even ideology.

1939
02:03:59,032 --> 02:04:01,902
人们会为彼此献出生命，
People give their lives for one another,

1940
02:04:03,436 --> 02:04:07,240
为自由选择生活的方式
和为上帝而献身
for the freedom to live those lives as they choose and for God.

1941
02:04:11,344 --> 02:04:12,613
我们剥夺了这一点
We took that away.

1942
02:04:15,381 --> 02:04:16,483
十字军战士...
The Crusader...

1943
02:04:18,418 --> 02:04:19,586
把它还给了他们
gave it back to them.

1944
02:04:31,031 --> 02:04:33,767
这就是你问题的答案
And that is the answer to your question.

1945
02:04:37,638 --> 02:04:39,673
谢谢你，维克多·彼得罗维奇
Thank you, Viktor Petrovich.

1946
02:04:55,889 --> 02:04:56,823
拿去吧
Take it.

1947
02:05:02,963 --> 02:05:03,930
谢谢
Thank you.

1948
02:05:06,299 --> 02:05:07,433
晚安
Good night.

1949
02:05:37,297 --> 02:05:39,065
总统先生，那里发生了什么？
What's going on there, Mr. President?

1950
02:05:42,035 --> 02:05:43,904
这对我来说意义重大
This means something to me.

1951
02:05:46,039 --> 02:05:47,708
我知道你在说什么，约翰，
I know what you're saying, John,

1952
02:05:48,675 --> 02:05:50,376
但我不会那么做的
but I'm not gonna do it.

1953
02:05:50,510 --> 02:05:53,079
夫人，我需要你告诉他我们不能再这样做了
Ma'am, I need you to tell him we can't do this anymore.

1954
02:05:53,213 --> 02:05:56,016
我不能我不能我做不到
I can't. I can't. I can't do it.

1955
02:05:57,818 --> 02:05:59,352
他昨天迷路了
He got lost yesterday.

1956
02:06:00,153 --> 02:06:01,855
我半个小时都找不到他
I couldn't find him for half an hour.

1957
02:06:02,723 --> 02:06:05,759
马知道骑手不知道
自己在做什么，好吗？他...
Horses know when a rider doesn't know what he's doing, okay? He's...

1958
02:06:06,993 --> 02:06:08,328
他会再次被摔下来的
He's gonna get thrown again.

1959
02:06:09,830 --> 02:06:12,498
我不能告诉他不能再骑马了
I can't tell him that he can't ride anymore.

1960
02:06:14,968 --> 02:06:16,436
他太喜欢骑马了
He loves it too much.

1961
02:06:18,304 --> 02:06:19,239
拜托
Please.

1962
02:06:23,076 --> 02:06:24,044
好吧
Okay.

1963
02:06:30,483 --> 02:06:32,252
他更爱你，夫人
He loves you more, ma'am.

1964
02:06:52,072 --> 02:06:53,239
总统先生？
Mr. President?

1965
02:06:55,876 --> 02:06:57,243
怎么了，约翰？
What is it, John?

1966
02:07:00,446 --> 02:07:01,481
你知道，呃...
You know, uh...

1967
02:07:03,049 --> 02:07:06,286
我觉得我们骑马的乐趣
已经不如从前了
I don't think we're having as much fun riding as we used to.

1968
02:07:07,453 --> 02:07:09,622
哦，负责里根夫人的特工，她...
Oh, the agent on, uh...

1969
02:07:09,756 --> 02:07:12,125
- 负责里根夫人的特工，她...
- 你想说什么，约翰？
- On Mrs. Reagan, she is... - What do you want, John?

1970
02:07:17,297 --> 02:07:18,665
总统先生，我认为...
Mr. President, I don't--

1971
02:07:20,033 --> 02:07:21,835
我认为我们不应该再骑马了
I don't think we should ride anymore.

1972
02:07:24,871 --> 02:07:25,772
哦
Oh.

1973
02:07:54,167 --> 02:07:55,268
再骑一次
One more ride.

1974
02:07:59,105 --> 02:08:00,473
好的，总统先生
Yes, sir, Mr. President.

1975
02:08:06,479 --> 02:08:07,380
嗯
Mm.

1976
02:08:47,687 --> 02:08:49,722
亲爱的美国同胞们
My fellow Americans.

1977
02:08:49,890 --> 02:08:53,894
我最近被告知
我是数百万美国人中的一员，
I have recently been told that I am one of the millions of Americans

1978
02:08:54,060 --> 02:08:57,663
将会患上阿尔茨海默症
who will be afflicted with Alzheimer's disease.

1979
02:08:57,831 --> 02:09:01,434
此刻，我感觉很好
At the moment, I feel just fine.

1980
02:09:01,434 --> 02:09:05,038
我打算在上帝赐予我的余生里，
I intend to live the remainder of the years God gives me

1981
02:09:05,205 --> 02:09:07,240
继续做我一直在做的事情
doing the things,I have always done.

1982
02:09:08,341 --> 02:09:12,412
不幸的是
随着阿尔茨海默症的进展，
Unfortunately, as Alzheimer's disease progresses,

1983
02:09:12,578 --> 02:09:15,916
家人常常要承担沉重的负担
the family often bears a heavy burden.

1984
02:09:16,082 --> 02:09:19,485
我只希望有某种方法能让南希
I only wish there was some way,I could spare Nancy

1985
02:09:19,652 --> 02:09:22,889
免受这种痛苦的经历
from this painful experience.

1986
02:09:23,056 --> 02:09:25,158
我将继续与我深爱的南希
I will continue to share life's journey

1987
02:09:25,325 --> 02:09:28,594
和我的家人一起分享人生旅程
with my beloved Nancy and my family.

1988
02:09:28,761 --> 02:09:31,164
我计划享受大自然，
I plan to enjoy the great outdoors

1989
02:09:31,331 --> 02:09:34,734
并与我的朋友和支持者保持联系
and stay in touch with my friends and supporters.

1990
02:09:36,002 --> 02:09:37,703
当那一刻来临时，
When the time comes,

1991
02:09:37,871 --> 02:09:40,841
我相信在你们的帮助下，
I am confident that with your help,

1992
02:09:41,007 --> 02:09:43,409
她会以信念和勇气面对
she will face it with faith and courage.

1993
02:10:49,775 --> 02:10:53,846
最后，让我感谢你们，美国人民，
In closing, let me thank you, the American people,

1994
02:10:54,014 --> 02:10:56,116
给予我莫大的荣幸
for giving me the great honor

1995
02:10:56,282 --> 02:10:58,885
让我能够担任你们的总统
of allowing me to serve as your president.

1996
02:10:59,819 --> 02:11:04,024
当上帝召唤我回家时，无论何时，
When the Lord calls me home, whenever that may be,

1997
02:11:04,190 --> 02:11:07,527
我将带着对这个国家最深沉的爱
I will leave with the greatest love for this country of ours

1998
02:11:07,693 --> 02:11:11,297
和对其未来永恒的乐观离去
and eternal optimism for its future.

1999
02:11:11,464 --> 02:11:16,002
我现在开始了一段
将引领我走向人生黄昏的旅程
I now begin the journey that will lead me into the sunset of my life.

2000
02:11:16,136 --> 02:11:17,938
我知道对美国来说，
I know that for America,

2001
02:11:18,104 --> 02:11:21,207
前方永远会有光明的新黎明
there will always be a bright new dawn ahead.

2002
02:11:22,175 --> 02:11:24,010
谢谢你们，我的朋友们
Thank you, my friends.

2003
02:11:24,177 --> 02:11:26,079
愿上帝永远保佑你们
May God always bless you.

2004
02:11:27,713 --> 02:11:29,049
诚挚地，
Sincerely,

2005
02:11:30,650 --> 02:11:31,817
罗纳德·里根
Ronald Reagan.

